I have been obsessed with hair since I was a kid literally😆

All my baby dolls hair was laid…
Then I got good enough to where my family start letting me play in their hair and turned it up a notch, I started installing Quickweaves and sew ins and fell in love. 
…
I started working in the shop with my aunt as her assistant doing the shampoos, blow drying, and prepping her clients to sit in her chair. Once I saw how much you can make being a hairstylist and how you can work on your time and be creative I instantly knew I was gonna be a hairstylist 
…
I was determined to be to goat too lol. I even learned how to do my very 1st frontal install off YouTube 20 minutes before she was supposed to come. Ain’t bleach it or nothing y’all😆😆 but I did let her know I never did a frontal tho so we both knew it was practice.
…
But I kept hustling, stayed consistent and kept going and look at me out her Slaying Celebs and working on TV Shows and shit🤗

Who would have thought😝
But I’m forever Grateful ❤️🙏🏾

If I can do it You can do it too💪🏾

Installed This Kinky Straight Frontal Wig from @lovelavishluxe and I absolutely LOVE this hair texture😍♥️

Here’s some things you should know about Kinky Straight Hair

1. The Kinky Straight Texture Is similar to a natural blowout Style.

2. This hair flat irons flawlessly and gets super straight however it does act like a natural blowout as well meaning if there is humidity or moisture in the air the hair will swell back up!! 

3. The Hair Curls perfectly however, they will drop faster, unless you set the curls by pinning them up. 

I personally love the hair but there is maintenance necessary to keep certain looks when wearing. If you don’t mind straightening or curling up your hair up on a daily basis then you will absolutely love the kinky straight hair too.

Tips To Avoid Burnout😮‍💨
Hairstylist Edition💞

 FACT: Burnout is a serious issue that can affect hairstylists due to the demands of the job.

And I’m not gone lie Ya girl been doing hair so long I have experienced several periods of burnt out😫🤣
When I first started hairstyling was a hustle, 
Always chasing the bag, NEVER said No, no matter what prior  activities I may have had going on at the time, Booked Back to Back💃🏾 All that. 
…And I still have that same hustle mentality except I learned that when you get burnt out, you can’t really do sh:t foreal. I had to learn to organize and manage my time way better because I was getting money but I was also tired AF. 
These tips may sound simple but they really helped me and 

it’s also the little things that count the most because just these small steps to remind you to take time for yourself can be a game changer.

avoiding burnout is a personal journey, and it may require trial and error to find the strategies that work best for you. What’s most Important tho “Prioritize your well-being”❤️

Tag your hairstylist friend or save this post to remind yourself of these tips for Later🥰

Loving the Skin Im in forealllllllll😍😍. Y’all Ready for this YouTube Era or Naw because ya girl been taking a little break to get my business, my life, these classes, and my content together and now it’s time to drop this ish😝

The keys to making the lace look like it’s really coming out of the scalp: 1. Having good Lace, the thinner the better. 2. Bleaching and Toning the knots so that no black dots are showing at the lace base. The toning removes any brassy or copper/ orangish color tones.
